---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="PID Motor Project">
  <section class="p-8 sm:p-12 md:p-16 lg:p-24 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <a href="/#projects" class="text-sm text-gray-500 hover:underline">
      ← Back to Home
    </a>

    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900">
      PID Motor Controller
    </h1>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-6">
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg text-sm">Electrical Design</span>
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg text-sm">Prototyping</span>
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg text-sm">Digital Logic</span>
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg text-sm">FETs</span>
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg text-sm">Latches</span>
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg text-sm">Counters</span>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mt-8">
      <img src="/motor1.jpg" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <img src="/motor3.jpg" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <img src="/motor2.jpg" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        In this project, a closed-loop servo control system was designed, built,
        tested, and integrated to actively control the rotational speed of a DC
        motor using analog and digital electronics.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure class="mt-8">
      <img src="/p1.png" alt="Schematic" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
        Fig. 1: Project schematic
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <figure class="mt-8">
      <img src="/p2.png" alt="Final build" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
        Fig. 2: Final circuit result
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div class="mt-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        The system measured motor speed using an optical sensor consisting of an
        LED, a phototransistor, and a slotted rotating disc attached to the motor
        shaft.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        A timing control circuit generated synchronized LATCH and RESET signals
        from a 5 Hz square-wave input, ensuring controlled data capture.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure class="mt-8">
      <img src="/p3.png" alt="Latch schematic" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
        Fig. 3: Latch and reset schematic
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div class="mt-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        An 8-bit digital counter built from cascaded divide-by-16 counters counted
        rotation pulses between reset intervals.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-8">
      <figure>
        <img src="/p4.png" alt="Counter integration" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Fig. 4: Counter integration
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure>
        <img src="/p5.png" alt="Counter output" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Fig. 5: Counter output
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        The digital speed value was converted to an analog voltage using an R–2R
        ladder DAC.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure class="mt-8">
      <img src="/p6.png" alt="DAC" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
        Fig. 6: DAC pinout
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

  
    <div class="mt-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        An error amplifier compared the measured speed to a setpoint and regulated
        motor current using a power BJT.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure class="mt-8">
      <img src="/p8.png" alt="Error amplifier" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
        Fig. 8: Error amplifier circuit
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div class="mt-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        The complete system demonstrated stable closed-loop RPM control.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-8">
      <figure>
        <img src="/p9.png" alt="Motor schematic" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Fig. 9: Motor control schematic
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure>
        <img src="/p10.png" alt="Final circuit" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Fig. 10: Final circuit
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-12 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
      Lab notebook excerpts
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
      <img src="/n1.png" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <img src="/n2.png" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <img src="/n3.png" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <img src="/n4.png" class="w-full rounded-md shadow-lg" />
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
